This is the example of deploy simple node js app

1. Install and config git.
2. Install and config aws cli.
3. Install npm.

4. Install Jenkins:
5. Config SMTP.
6. Add AWS private key in Credentials block - SSH Username "ubuntu" with private key.
7. Add Jenkins item using pipline file. 
8.1. Modify KEY_PAIR value - your key pair name in AWS.
8.2. Modify MAIL_TO value - your email.
8.3. Add creds from the previous point as parameter named "USER_KEY" to the Build.

* if you have EC2 instance in Terminated state, U should delete its Tag named "unique_id"
